# Gemma Pizza Project - Cursor Rules

## 🎯 Stack & Technologies

- **Framework:** Next.js 15 (App Router)
- **ORM:** Prisma
- **Database:** Supabase PostgreSQL
- **Language:** TypeScript
- **State Management:** Zustand
- **Styling:** TailwindCSS
- **Auth:** NextAuth.js
- **Payment:** Stripe

---

## 🗄️ Database Configuration (Supabase)

### Connection Strings

```
# API Routes - use Pooler (Transaction mode)
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://[user]:[password]@[host]:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true"

# Migrations - use Direct connection
DIRECT_URL="postgresql://[user]:[password]@[host]:5432/postgres"
```

### Connection Best Practices

- ✅ Always use Pooler (pgbouncer=true) for API routes
- ✅ Use Direct URL only for Prisma migrations
- ✅ Set connection_limit=10 in production
- ✅ Set pool_timeout=30
- ✅ Close connections properly
- ❌ Never use Direct connection in API routes (exhausts connection pool)

### Performance Settings

```typescript
// prisma/schema.prisma
datasource db {
  provider          = "postgresql"
  url               = env("DATABASE_URL")      // Pooler for queries
  directUrl         = env("DIRECT_URL")        // Direct for migrations
  shadowDatabaseUrl = env("SHADOW_DATABASE_URL")
}

generator client {
  provider        = "prisma-client-js"
  previewFeatures = ["postgresqlExtensions"]
}
```

---

## ⚡ Performance Best Practices

### 1. Prisma Query Optimization

#### ✅ ALWAYS use `select` instead of `include`:

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - loads all fields
const product = await prisma.product.findFirst({
  include: { ingredients: true },
});

// ✅ GOOD - loads only needed fields
const product = await prisma.product.findFirst({
  select: {
    id: true,
    name: true,
    imageUrl: true,
    ingredients: {
      select: { id: true, name: true, price: true },
    },
  },
});
```

#### ✅ Use React.cache() for Server Components:

```typescript
import { cache } from 'react';

export const findPizzas = cache(async (params) => {
  return await prisma.category.findMany({...});
});
```

#### ✅ Avoid N+1 queries:

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - N+1 problem
for (const item of items) {
  const product = await prisma.product.findUnique({ where: { id: item.productId } });
}

// ✅ GOOD - single query with include/select
const items = await prisma.cartItem.findMany({
  select: {
    id: true,
    productItem: {
      select: { product: { select: { name: true } } },
    },
  },
});
```

### 2. Database Indexes

#### Always index frequently queried fields:

```sql
-- Already created
CREATE INDEX "Cart_tokenId_idx" ON "Cart"("tokenId");
CREATE INDEX "CartItem_cartId_idx" ON "CartItem"("cartId");
CREATE INDEX "CartItem_productItemId_idx" ON "CartItem"("productItemId");
CREATE INDEX "CartItem_compositionKey_idx" ON "CartItem"("compositionKey");
CREATE INDEX "Product_categoryId_idx" ON "Product"("categoryId");

-- Composite indexes for complex queries
CREATE INDEX "CartItem_cartId_productItemId_idx" ON "CartItem"("cartId", "productItemId");
```

### 3. API Route Caching

#### Add revalidate to API routes:

```typescript
// For rarely changing data (ingredients, categories)
export const revalidate = 3600; // 1 hour

// For frequently changing data (stories)
export const revalidate = 1800; // 30 minutes

// For user-specific data (cart)
export const revalidate = 5; // 5 seconds
```

#### In-memory cache for static data:

```typescript
let cachedData: any[] | null = null;
let cacheTime = 0;
const CACHE_TTL = 3600 * 1000; // 1 hour

export async function GET() {
  const now = Date.now();

  if (cachedData && (now - cacheTime) < CACHE_TTL) {
    return NextResponse.json(cachedData);
  }

  cachedData = await prisma.ingredient.findMany({...});
  cacheTime = now;

  return NextResponse.json(cachedData);
}
```

### 4. Server Components Optimization

#### Use revalidate for page caching:

```typescript
// app/page.tsx
export const revalidate = 60; // cache for 60 seconds

export default async function Home() {
  const data = await findPizzas();
  return <div>{/* ... */}</div>;
}
```

